@Dan @amundson @jsmitchell @agunde:

I suggested using 0edde5778c647ffc9f424297e59d6ad14cb2e98d because it includes the new consensus api changes and is the commit that @pschwarz , @boydjohnson, and myself have done the most long-running testing with. I am fine with jumping ahead to include doc changes and the separation of the PoET repo.

I am less comfortable recommending the release of the subsequent changes to integrate the block manager and rewrite the block validator in Rust. There is a known performance issue with these changes that we have been investigating and that should be resolved before including these changes in a release. I would like to include these changes in a 1.1.2 or 1.2 release once the issue has been resolved.

